column1:
I am here to tell you that there are people who have never been defeated. They are the ones who never fought. They managed to avoid scars, humiliations, and feelings of helplessness, as well as those moments when even Warriors doubt the existence of God. Such people can say with pride: â€œI never lost a battle.â€On the other hand, they will never be able to say: â€œI won a battle.â€
Not that they care.They live in a universe in which they believe they are invulnerable; they close their eyes to injustices and to suffering; they feel safe because they do not have to deal with the daily challenges faced by those who risk stepping out beyond their own boundaries.â€Those who were never defeated seem happy and superior, masters of a truth they never had to lift a finger to achieve. They are always on the side of the strong. Theyâ€™re like hyenas, who eat only the leavings of lions. They teach their children: â€œDonâ€™t get involved in conflicts; youâ€™ll only lose. Keep your doubts to yourself and youâ€™ll never have any problems. If someone attacks you, donâ€™t get offended or demean yourself by hitting back. There are more important things in life.
â€In the silence of the night, they fight their imaginary battles: their unrealized dreams, the injustices to which they turned a blind eye, the moments of cowardice they managed to conceal from other peopleâ€”but not from themselvesâ€”and the love that crossed their path with a sparkle in its eyes, the love God had intended for them, but Which they lacked the courage to embrace. And they promise themselves: â€œTomorrow will be different.â€But tomorrow comes and the paralyzing question surfaces in their mind: â€œWhat if it doesnâ€™t work out?â€And so they do nothing.
 Woe to those who were never beaten! They will never be winners in this life.
by Paulo Coelho - Manuscript Found in Accra
